I have eaten a lot of both and these were pretty close to the top. I would have liked a better quality non-alcoholic beer, however. Sharp's is as close to the bottom as you can get. How about a Beck's or, at least, a Clausthaler. The service could not have been better - so friendly and helpful.

Hidden gem. Authentic Mexican cuisine with all the dishes you know and then some. Guac and margaritas are great. Salsa is spicy so ask for mild if you don't like heat. Their chips are home made and probably some of the best I've had... I've lived in LA so that is a solid recommendation. Salud!
Excellent food, service, drinks. Both times I have had dinner here, the owner came by to check on our table. Highly recommend for 3rd dates, families and girls' nights out.

Still kicking myself that we lived less than a block away from Mas Alla del Sol and didn't eat here for months after moving to Edgewater. It's one of the best Mexican restaurants on the north side. The staff is friendly but not pushy, the drinks are tasty but not overpowering, and the food has great flavors regardless of what you order. One of the best restaurants on N Broadway.

Just had brunch here. The food was delicious, fresh, and authentic. The service by Nana was excellent and prompt. We had the huevos rancheros, huevos a la mexicana, and fried plantains with some coffee, coconut flan, and lava cake. This is by far my favorite Mexican restaurant in the city.
